author: pderop
msg: Added support for parallelism in dependency manager: We can now optionally use a DispatchExecutor instead of the default
SerialExecutor.  The key difference with the SerialExecutor is that several DispatchQueues can be executed in parallel
inside a shared thread pool. When one thread schedules some tasks in DispatchQueue Q1, Q2, then Q1/Q2 queues are dispatched
and executed concurrently in a shared thread pool. But each queue will executing tasks scheduled in it serially, in FIFO order.
